      <h2>Telecommunications Expert Witness: In-Depth Expertise</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Expertise  in telecommunications topologies, network protocols, and communications technologies<br>Expertise in telecommunications topologies, network protocols, and communications technologies (HTTP, SNMP, TCP/IP, FTP, TDM, DWDM, SONET, WAN, LAN, Ethernet, ATM, <a href="/us-10598764-radar-target-detection-and-imaging-system-for-autonomous-car/">Wireless</a>, etc.). Expert in a broad range of current telecommunications technology, including hardware, software, server operating systems, networking, internet/intranet development, deployment, utilization, and telecommunications. Knowledge of voice and data circuits and video technology.</li>
        <li>The Essence of Telecommunications Expertise<br>Dr. Lavian&rsquo;s extensive expertise in the multifaceted telecommunications domain is crucial for an expert witness in complex legal cases. His expertise spans the entire spectrum of technologies transmitting information across vast distances, from foundational systems like the public switched telephone network (PSTN) to modern advancements like the internet and cellular networks.</li>
        <li>The Backbone of Communication: Public Switched Telephone Network (PSTN)<br>PSTN, the cornerstone of traditional voice communication, relies on circuit-switched networks and physical cables to connect calls and transmit data in real-time. Dr. Lavian&rsquo;s command over PSTN&rsquo;s intricacies and evolution is vital in legal disputes involving legacy telecom systems.</li>
        <li>Circuit Switching: The Classic Method of Connectivity<br>Dr. Lavian&rsquo;s deep understanding of circuit switching, the traditional technique for establishing dedicated communication paths, plays a significant role in analyzing and explaining older telecommunications technologies in a legal setting.</li>
        <li>Packet Switching: The Bedrock of Modern Communications<br>With packet switching&rsquo;s pivotal role in current and future communications, Dr. Lavian&rsquo;s expertise ensures a comprehensive grasp of how data packets operate over the Internet and other digital networks, highlighting his versatility as a telecommunications expert witness.</li>
        <li>Synchronous Optical Networking (SONET/SDH)<br>Dr. Lavian&rsquo;s analysis of SONET and SDH protocols delves into their significance in high-speed data transmission, a subject of increasing relevance in patent litigations that touch on the core of telecommunications infrastructure.</li>
        <li>Signaling System 7 (SS7): The Signaling Protocol of Telecommunications<br>Understanding SS7 is imperative for managing the setup and termination of telecom sessions. Dr. Lavian&rsquo;s familiarity with SS7 is essential for providing authoritative expertise in traditional and cellular network communications cases.</li>
        <li>Cellular Systems: From Foundations to Future<br>His comprehensive understanding of the evolution of cellular systems is a testament to his ability to address the intricacies of mobile communications in legal disputes, particularly in patent litigation, where the focus often falls on the proprietary technologies that define the industry&rsquo;s competitive edge.</li>
